LOUIS JADOT BEAUJOLAIS VILLAGES 1974

Achieving and maintaining renown as one of the great wine merchants of Burgundy is no mean trick. Louis Jadot has done it for decades. A taste of the 1974 Beaujolais Villages he sends us gives ample proof of his integrity. Replete with heady fruit, re- splendent in a bright purple robe, this is truly a top-flight Beaujolais—one from the very successful 1974 har- vest. Try drinking this slightly cool — you'll imagine your- self amid the lusty vineyards themselves.
